\strong{Absolute vs relative targets}

Absolute targets are stored directly as absolute thresholds:
\deqn{
T_f = t_f,
}
where \eqn{t_f} is the value supplied by the user.

Relative targets are supplied as proportions \eqn{r_f \in [0,1]} and are
converted into absolute thresholds using the current baseline total amount of
each feature:
\deqn{
T_f = r_f \times B_f,
}
where \eqn{B_f} is the current total amount of feature \eqn{f} in the
landscape, computed by \code{.pa_feature_totals()}.

